Tepco Says Hydrogen Explosion at Fukushima No.1 Nuclear Unit Is Unlikely

-- B y   M i c h i o   N a k a y a m a
-- 
2011-04-11T03:14:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/tepco-says-hydrogen-explosion-at-fukushima-no-1-nuclear-unit-is-unlikely.html
Tokyo Electric Power Co. said the
probability of a hydrogen explosion at the Fukushima Dai-Ichi
No. 1 reactor is low after nitrogen injections prevented a rise
in hydrogen and oxygen pressure.  Hikaru Kuroda, head of nuclear maintenance at the Japanese
utility, made the comments today at a press conference.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Michio Nakayama in Tokyo at 
 mnakayama4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
